":"1301–Overleden","1330–Female":"1330–Overleden","1337":"1337","1301":"1301","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England"},"en":{"1330–":"1330–Deceased","1296–Male":"1296–Deceased","1301–Male":"1301–Deceased","1330–Female":"1330–Deceased","1337":"1337","1301":"1301","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ralpeigh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Raleigh (House) in Pilton (Devon), recorded as <i>Radeleia</i> in 1086 and <i>Rawlegh</i> in 1535. The placename probably derives from Old English <i>rǣge</i> ‘roe deer’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Irish: variant of   Riley  .","History: The English explorer Sir Walter Raleigh (1554–1618) was born in Hayes Barton, Devon, into a family of Devon gentry. He was related to most of the West Country's important families, including that of Sir Francis Drake. His half-brother was the explorer Sir Humphrey Gilbert. In 1578 Raleigh was granted a patent to explore and colonize “unknown lands” in America. In the 1580s he was granted extensive estates in Munster (Ireland), in reward for his suppression of the Desmond Rebellions."],"variants":[{"name":"Raley","meanings":["English: variant of   Raleigh  ."]},{"name":"Rawleigh","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Erwin, Orlo.","English: variant of   Raleigh  , reflecting a common pronunciation."]},{"name":"Riley","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): habitational name chiefly from High Ryley in Accrington (Lancashire) and Riley in Kirkburton, which was in the manor of Wakefield (Yorkshire). In some cases the name may derive from Riley Farm in Eyam (Derbyshire), Royley in Royton (Lancashire), or Rylah in Scarcliffe (Derbyshire). The placenames all come from Old English <i>rȳge</i> ‘rye’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Irish: from <b>Ó Raghailligh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Raghailleach</i>’, Old Irish <i>Roghallach</i>. This is the name of a chieftain family in Cavan, related to the O'Rourkes. In Anglicized form it has also been confused with <b>Ó Raithile</b> found in Munster, usually Anglicized as <b>O'Rahilly</b> or   Rahilly  . See   O'Reilly  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705193,"age":7,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705195,"age":52,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Ralpeigh was born in 1330, in Sussex, England. She had at least 1 son with Reginald Rankyn."},"et":{"1330–":"1330–Surnud","1296–Male":"1296–Surnud","1301–Male":"1301–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1337":"1337","1301":"1301","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England"},"fi":{"1330–":"1330–Kuollut","1296–Male":"1296–Kuollut","1301–Male":"1301–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1301":"1301","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England"},"fr":{"1330–":"1330–Décédée","1296–Male":"1296–Décédé","1301–Male":"1301–Décédé","1330–Female":"1330–Décédée","1337":"1337","1301":"1301","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","Sussex, England":"Sussex, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Alice Ralpeigh est née en 1330, à Sussex, Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Reginald Rankyn."},"de":{"1330–":"1330–Verstorben","1296–Male":"1296–Verstorben","1301–Male":"1301–Verstorben","1330–Female":"1330–Verstorben","1337":"1337","1301":"1301","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England","lifeSummary":"Alice Ralpeigh wurde 1330 in Sussex, England geboren. Sie hatte mit Reginald Rankyn mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1330–":"1330–Desede","1296–Male":"1296–Desede","1301–Male":"1301–Desede","1330–Female":"1330–Desede","1337":"1337","1301":"1301","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England"},"hu":{"1330–":"1330–elhunyt","1296–Male":"1296–elhunyt","1301–Male":"1301–elhunyt","1330–Female":"1330–elhunyt","1337":"1337","1301":"1301","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England"},"id":{"1330–":"1330–Telah Meninggal","1296–Male":"1296–Telah Meninggal","1301–Male":"1301–Telah Meninggal","1330–Female":"1330–Telah Meninggal","1337":"1337","1301":"1301","1453":"1453","1330":"1330","1296":"1296","1382":"1382","Sussex, England":"Sussex, England"},"it":{"1330–":"1330–Deceduta","1296–Male":"129